					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Roth wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">It kind of makes me wonder if there is a time when polling $2002 on the NES is acceptable</div>
<br />Soon after power-on, in order to make sure the PPU reset finished all the way. The typical sequence is poll $2002, clear CPU RAM, poll $2002, set palette, clear nametables. There's about a 1 out of 21 chance that you'll get lag on any frame; this chance is acceptable in something like power-on. But after that, use NMI.</div>

