				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">frantik wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">is there a reason it's better to increment a variable inside of vblanks iterrupt routine and then handle the variable change, vs just putting the  handling code between the interrupt vector and the RTI?</div>
<br />No, except that the pattern of an ISR that just sets a flag might be more familiar to developers on platforms where you don't get to write your own ISRs, such as any multitasking OS. You could put the entire game in the NMI; Super Mario Bros. does just this. Just make sure you do the PPU updates as soon as possible after the start of vblank, which means before you run the sound engine.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

