			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Polling the VBL count is simpler to code for, because you don't have to deal with re-entrancy and concurrency issues. If the code is executed from NMI, you need a flag to tell it when it can run, and where it's called from the mainline code is less-clear. Unless you're doing split-screen effects, you don't need code guaranteed to run every NMI, so the polling approach is better.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

